begin
reserve a for Nat;
reserve m for Nat;
theorem
(((a <> ( 0 ) & m is  prime) & a,m are_relative_prime ) implies ( ( a |^ m ) mod m ) = ( a mod m ))
proof
assume that
A1: a <> ( 0 )
and
A2: m is  prime
and
A3: a,m are_relative_prime ;
A4: m > 1 by A2,INT_2:def 4;
then ( m - 1 ) > ( 1 - 1 ) by XREAL_1:9;
then reconsider mm = ( m - 1 ) as (Element of ( NAT )) by INT_1:3;
( Euler m ) = ( m - 1 ) by A2,EULER_1:20;
then ( ( ( a |^ mm ) mod m ) * a ) = ( 1 * a ) by A1,A3,A4,CKB24:1;
then (( mm + 1 ) = m & ( ( ( a |^ mm ) * a ) mod m ) = ( a mod m )) by CKB11:1;
hence thesis by NEWTON:6;
end;
